 5. What is the difference between exporting data as SQL and Excel?


| Aspect    | SQL Export                             | Excel Export                     |

| --------- | -------------------------------------- | -------------------------------- |

| Content   | Schema + Data (CREATE TABLE + INSERTs) | Data only (tabular rows/columns) |

| Purpose   | Full backup/reimport to any MySQL      | Analysis/sharing/visualization   |

| Format    | .sql text file                         | .xlsx/.csv spreadsheet           |

| Size      | Compact (binary possible)              | Larger (formatting overhead)     |

| Restore   | mysql -u root < backup.sql             | Import wizard/manual             |

| Tools     | Database migration                     | Excel/Power BI/Tableau           |

| Structure | Preserves keys/constraints             | Flattens relationships           |


SQL = complete database clone; Excel = human-readable data slice.





